aspx?path=Error,%20invalid%20input%3A%20with%20expects%20its%201st%20a
rgument,%20pname,%20to%20be%20of%20type%20%7B%60module%60,%20package%7
D,%20but%20received%20shareman" "" }{TEXT 319 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "
> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 22 " precision := double :" }}}}{SECT 0 {PARA 
213 "" 0 "" {TEXT 226 32 " Summary and governing equations" }{TEXT 
270 0 "" }}{SECT 0 {PARA 5 "" 0 "" {TEXT 320 20 " Governing equation "
 }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 318 47 "The governing equation solved is of t
he form :\n" }{TEXT 271 38 "theta(x)*dC/dt = -d(Fdiff+Fadv)/dx + R" }
{TEXT 318 2 ",\n" }{TEXT 318 7 "where \n" }{TEXT 318 69 "- dX/dp is th
e partial derivative of X with respect to p [M/L^3/[p]]\n" }{TEXT 318 
84 "- theta(x) = A(x)*por(x) for dissolved, and A(x)*(1-por(x)) for so
lid species [L^2]\n" }{TEXT 318 43 "- Fdiff = -(D(x)*theta(x)*dC/dx) [
M/L^2/T]\n" }{TEXT 318 34 "- Fadv  = (v*theta(x)*C)[M/L^2/T]\n" }{TEXT
 318 57 "- A is the cross section area [L^2], por is porosity [-]\n" }
{TEXT 318 49 "- v is the advection velocity [L/T], the sum of \n" }
{TEXT 318 85 "the water flow velocity (vwat = water flow q in [L^3/T]/
theta(x), solutes only) and \n" }{TEXT 318 105 "an advective velocity \+
w acting upon both solids and solutes (e.g. movement due to fixed refe
rence frame)\n" }{TEXT 318 64 "- D is the effective diffusion coeffici
ent [L^2/T], the sum of \n" }{TEXT 318 59 "the molecular diffusion coe
fficient (Dmol, solutes only), \n" }{TEXT 318 39 "the bioturbation coe
fficient (Db) and \n" }{TEXT 318 73 "the dispersion coefficient (Disp \+
= aL*|vwat|, solutes only, aL in [L]). \n" }{TEXT 318 101 "- R is the \+
sum of the reaction terms [M/L^3/T] as specified in the reaction netwo
rk established below" }}}{SECT 0 {PARA 5 "" 0 "" {TEXT 320 9 " Caveats
 " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 318 60 "- for real numbers you should add a
 point after the number.\n" }{TEXT 318 30 "- make sure all units match
. \n" }{TEXT 318 68 "e.g. rates and dXdt, or flux boundary conditions \+
and concentrations\n" }{TEXT 318 46 "for the conversion of solid to so
lute units, \n" }{TEXT 318 76 "one may define temporary variables that
 can be used in the rate laws below:\n" }{TEXT 318 49 "s_dens := 2.5; \+
# solid density in [g/cm_solid^3]\n" }{TEXT 318 48 "sd := 1000. * s_de
ns * (1. - por(j)) / por(j); \n" }{TEXT 318 66 "the factor 1.d03 conve
rts cm^3 to liter, e.g. [g/cm^3] to [g/l]. \n" }{TEXT 318 40 "note tha
t you need to refer to porosity " }{TEXT 272 7 "exactly" }{TEXT 318 
11 " as por(j)." }}}}{SECT 0 {PARA 3 "" 0 "" {TEXT 321 21 " Physics - \+
Parameters" }}{PARA 206 "" 0 "" {TEXT 322 19 "The list of length " }
{TEXT 26 20 "nparphys & nparphys2" }{TEXT 322 13 " is given by " }
{TEXT 26 22 "phys_name & phys_name2" }{TEXT 322 26 "; the values colle
cted in " }{TEXT 26 21 "phys_val & phys_val2." }}{SECT 0 {PARA 5 "" 0 
"" {TEXT 320 33 " Spatial and temporal domain size" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT 26 9 "tot_time:" }{TEXT 318 43 " total length of simulation (T, \+
e.g. years)" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 26 10 "depth_max:" }{TEXT 318 60 
" spatial extent, e.g. total depth of simulation (L, e.g. cm)" }}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 18 "tot_time := 0.5 ;\n" }
{MPLTEXT 1 0 18 "depth_max := 0.1 ;" }{MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}{PARA 11 "" 
1 "" {XPPMATH 20 ">I)tot_timeG6\"$\"\"&!\"\"" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" 
{XPPMATH 20 ">I*depth_maxG6\"$\"\"\"!\"\"" }}}}{SECT 0 {PARA 5 "" 0 ""
 {TEXT 320 23 " Transport coefficients" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT
 26 3 "vaL" }{TEXT 318 95 ": longitudinal dispersivity (L). The disper
sion coefficient is calculated as Disp = aL*|vwat| \n" }{TEXT 26 3 "vi
q" }{TEXT 318 82 ": depth dependency of flow. 0: constant, else changi
ng with depth (i.e. distance)\n" }{TEXT 26 3 "vq0" }{TEXT 318 53 ": wa
ter flow (either constant or else at x=0, L^3/T)\n" }{TEXT 26 3 "viw" 
}{TEXT 318 79 ": depth dependency of w. 0: constant, else changing wit
h depth (i.e. distance)\n" }{TEXT 26 3 "vw0" }{TEXT 318 89 ": advectio
n velocity working on solids and solutes (either constant or else at x
=0, L/T)\n" }{TEXT 26 4 "viDb" }{TEXT 318 80 ": depth dependency of Db
. 0: constant, else changing with depth (i.e. distance)\n" }{TEXT 26 
4 "vDb0" }{TEXT 318 97 ": bioturbation coefficient working on solids a
nd solutes (either constant or else at x=0, L^2/T)\n" }{TEXT 318 1 "\n
" }{TEXT 318 134 "- user specified profiles of q(x), w(x) or Db(x) mus
t be defined in the fortran subroutines advcoeff.f and diffcoeff.f, re
spectively.\n" }{TEXT 318 87 "- the molecular diffusion coefficients f
or the species used are specified further below" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> 
" 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 14 "val := 0.01 ;\n" }{MPLTEXT 1 0 11 "viq := 0 ;
\n" }{MPLTEXT 1 0 10 "vq0 := 0;\n" }{MPLTEXT 1 0 11 "viw := 0 ;\n" }
{MPLTEXT 1 0 73 "vw0 := 0 ; #1.0e-4 ; #in mm 10.0e-6*(1.4/Col_fac+(Col
_fac-1.0)/Col_fac);\n" }{MPLTEXT 1 0 12 "viDb := 0 ;\n" }{MPLTEXT 1 0 
13 "vDb0 := 0.0 ;" }{MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "
>I$valG6\"$\"\"\"!\"#" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 ">I$viqG6\"\"\"!
" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 ">I$vq0G6\"\"\"!" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" 
